{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] [[WP:NONFREE]] --> |name = Paula Froelich |pseudonym = |birth_date = October 30, 1973 |birth_place = Leeds, England |death_date = |death_place = |occupation = Novelist, columnist |genre = [[Fiction]] |movement = |influences = |influenced = | website = |signature = }} '''Paula Froelich''' is an American [[journalist]] and [[author]] of the [[book]] ''Mercury in Retrograde'', which appeared on the [[New York Times Best Seller]] list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/06/02/paula-froelich-talks-emme_n_210364.html|title=Paula Froelich Talks ''Mercury In Retrograde'' On "Today" Show (VIDEO)|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=26 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natja.memberclicks.net/2014-natja-awards-winners|title=2014 NATJA Awards Winners|last=Leon|first=Yanira|website=natja.memberclicks.net|language=en-us|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref>
Froelich was a [[newspaper columnist|columnist]] for the ''[[New York Post]]'' Page Six. Between March 31, 2014 and October 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title=Editor at large|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/paulafroelich|website=LinkedIn|accessdate=8 February 2016}}</ref> she was [[Editor in Chief]] of [[Yahoo Travel]], where she led [[editor]]ial direction, original content, and the expansion and re-imagination of the site. She is the founder of the website A Broad Abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://firstread.me/paula-froelich/|title=Traveler Tales: Paula Froelich - FirstRead.Me|date=2016-06-13|work=FirstRead.Me|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-US}}</ref> She is also working on a [[young adult novel|novel for young adults]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yahoo.tumblr.com/post/81327153931/yahoo-expands-editorial-staff-with-paula-froelich-and|title=Yahoo Expands Editorial Staff with Paula Froelich... - Yahoo|work=Yahoo|accessdate=26 February 2015}}</ref>
She was born in [[Leeds]], England in 1973 and grew up in [[Cincinnati]], Ohio. Her mother is Jewish.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/Pfro/status/950149446247026689}}</ref>
